intro: Laennecia confusa, commonly known as the confused laennecia, is a species of flowering plant in the family Apiaceae. It is native to South America, particularly found in Argentina and Chile. The plant is characterized by its slender, branched stems and small, white to pale yellow flowers arranged in umbels. Its leaves are finely divided, giving it a delicate appearance. Laennecia confusa is often found in dry, open habitats such as grasslands and rocky areas.
